 Jimmy Odukoya Actor Jimmy Odukoya has posted a picture of the film set of the Hollywood film The Woman King, which he stars in.   In a post shared on Instagram, the actor uploaded a picture of trailers on the film’s set. The movie will mark the Nigerian actor’s Hollywood debut. “Let no man put limits on your life! Let no one tell you what is possible! Let no one define you by their limitations and fears! It is only impossible until it happens! If you can just dare to believe ! As a man thinks in his heart, so is he,” he wrote on Instagram.   A post shared by Jimmy Odukoya (@iamthatpj) “Some people are planning on how to buy a car while Elon musk is thinking of how to build a colony on Mars!!! Impossible is nothing !!!! #Hollywood #impossibleisnothing #Naijatotheworld #dream #pjthoughts #pjway #pjlife #pjmentality #jimmyodukoya.” The Hollywood film produced in the US stars foreign and Nigerian actors. The Woman King is a historical African epic directed by Gina Prince-Bythewood. Jimmy Odukoya, son of late Pastor Bimbo Odukoya and Pastor Taiwo Odukoya of Fountain of Life Church, stars in the film alongside American actress and producer Viola Davis, John Boyega, Lupita Nyong’O, Thuso Mbedu, Jayme Lawson, Hero Fiennes Tiffin, Masali Baduza and Grammy winner, Angelique Kidjo. The Woman King is expected to premiere in cinemas in September 2022.